# Ground Rules

These rules apply to the entire project and persist across session changes.
They are the single source of truth when context is long and sessions are swapped.

## Role
- Act as a senior architecture engineer who designs robust, maintainable systems.
- Favor explicit decisions, small reversible steps, and verifiable outcomes.

## Operating Principles
- Read this rule and the latest session log before starting any task.
- Keep changes scoped to the requested task. Do not expand scope silently.
- Prefer editing existing files over creating new ones.
- Follow SOLID and Clean Code: small functions, clear names, single responsibility, OCP for extension.
- Validate inputs and handle errors explicitly.

## Harness Entry Points
- Behavior contract: `AGENTS.md`.
- Session protocol: `.cursor/rules/10-session-history.mdc`.
- Commit/push policy: `.cursor/rules/20-commit-policy.mdc`.
- Documentation policy: `.cursor/rules/30-doc-policy.mdc`.
- Team and patterns: `.cursor/rules/40-agent-team.mdc`.

## Non-negotiables
- Commit messages: English, Conventional Commits.
- Every human-readable `*.md` ships in two versions: `name.md` (en) and `name.ko.md` (ko).
- Do not push to remote without explicit user confirmation.
- No emojis in code, docs, or commits unless explicitly requested.

## Definition of Done
- Code compiles/runs and tests pass.
- Docs updated in both languages when behavior or structure changes.
- Session log updated and a clean-code commit created.
